utilb 1.0
Binaries for Linux prepared by faith@cs.unc.edu, Sun Dec 27 14:42:39 1992
Compiled with gcc 2.2.2d7 (-O6)
Linked with jump-4.1 libraries (-s -N), but tested with jump-4.2 libraries


To install from Linux binary distribution:

1) Get binary distribution (utilb10.taz) from
ftp.cs.unc.edu:/pub/faith/linux/utils or from
tsx-11.mit.edu:/pub/linux/binaries or from
2) cd /
3) gtar zpxvf utilb10.taz

Alternatively, the SLS sysinstall program can be used.



To uninstall this binary distribution, do the following:

cd /usr/src/utilb-1.0
./utilb10.Unins



To install from source:

1) Get source from:
   ftp.cs.unc.edu:/pub/faith/linux/utils/source/utilb-1.0.src.tar.Z
   or from tsx-11:/pub/linux/sources
2) Untar utilb-1.0.src.tar.Z in /usr/src
3) cd utilb-1.0
5) make
7) make install


Notes:

